    This 2025 summer, I am working at <a href="https://cmu-spuds.github.io/cmu-spuds-web/">SPUD Lab</a> at Carnegie Mellon University, advised by <a href="https://sauvik.me/">Prof. Sauvik Das</a>.
  </p>
  <h2 id='researchInterests'>Research Interest</h2>
  <p>
    My research interest lies in the interaction of Usable Privacy and Security, LLM Social Simulation, and Human-Centered AI. Specifically, I aim to focus on:
    <ul>
      <li>(1) developing effective simulation techniques that faithfully model user intentions and reasoning within real-world tasks.</li>
      <li>(2) mitigating privacy concerns on simulation personas by reducing sensitive data disclosure and increasing transparency and user control.</li>
      <li>(3) building personalized LLM agents based on high-fidelity, privacy-preserving simulations.</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

